    • EventController

      @Autowired public EventController(EventRepository eventRepository, UserRepository userRepository, EventService eventService, EventMapper eventMapper, com.speedment.jpastreamer.application.JPAStreamer jpaStreamer, JwtService jwtService)
      The EventController function is a REST controller that handles requests to the /events endpoint. It has methods for creating, updating, deleting and retrieving events from the database.
      Parameters:
      EventRepository - eventRepository Access the eventrepository
      UserRepository - userRepository Access the userrepository
      EventService - eventService Call the getallevents() method
      EventMapper - eventMapper Map the eventdto to an event object
      JPAStreamer - jpaStreamer Stream the data from the database
      JwtService - jwtService Get the userid from the jwt token

    • search

      @PostMapping("/search") public org.springframework.http.ResponseEntity<List<EventDto>> search(@RequestBody EventSearchRequest request)
      The search function takes in a request body of type EventSearchRequest, which is a class that contains the parameters for searching. The search function then calls the eventService's searchEvent method, passing in the request body as an argument. This returns a list of events that match those parameters. The list is then mapped to EventDto objects and returned with an HTTP status code of 200 (OK). If there are no matching events, it will return an empty arraylist with status code 200 (OK). Look searchEvent in eventservice
      Returns:
      A list of events that meet the search criteria
